---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Documentation" description="Documentation for netsert and netmodel - network automation tools">
  <h1>Documentation</h1>
  
  <p class="lead text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">
    Network automation tools that actually work. Built for engineers who are tired of vendor lock-in.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 not-prose">
    <a href="/docs/netsert/" class="block p-6 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg hover:border-gray-400 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">netsert</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Declarative network testing. Write YAML assertions, validate via gNMI.</p>
      <ul class="text-sm text-gray-500 space-y-1">
        <li>→ Assertion types (equals, contains, regex, exists)</li>
        <li>→ Generators for baseline creation</li>
        <li>→ Inventory groups & concurrency</li>
        <li>→ CI/CD integration</li>
      </ul>
    </a>

    <a href="/docs/netmodel/" class="block p-6 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg hover:border-gray-400 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">netmodel</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Extract network config to YAML. Your network as code, vendor-agnostic.</p>
      <ul class="text-sm text-gray-500 space-y-1">
        <li>→ Exporters (interfaces, BGP, OSPF, system, routing_policy)</li>
        <li>→ Ansible structure output</li>
        <li>→ Inventory groups</li>
        <li>→ OpenConfig-based extraction</li>
      </ul>
    </a>
  </div>

  <h2 class="mt-12">Quick Links</h2>
  
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://github.com/ndtobs/netsert">netsert on GitHub</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://github.com/ndtobs/netmodel">netmodel on GitHub</a></li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
